There are very few people who have reached out to me when I truly needed it. Who showed me what a special person I was when most had told me otherwise. Who can make me cry when I hear about all the love they have for me. Who has been there when everyone else had turned their backs to me. I can only think of maybe 2 people who have been there for me when I had nobody to hold onto. And in 2 days, I get to spend 5 days with one of them. There is no other way I want to spend my spring break than with such a special person. I'll see you on March 18, Kyle. 

And to the rest of you...Daz and Jessie mostly, text or call me and let me know how you guys are doing. I'm gonna miss ya both tons! Everyone else, have a great weekend or spring break and I'll be back with stories and pictures Wednesday!

MY HEAD HURTS! 
 
So I have about $950...$340 goes to my grandparents...122 to my dad...190 to my flight and 50 to my phone bill. And I put 100 in savings for my trip. Damn I'm good.

OMG OMG OMG I'm going Whale watching on Saturday! *claps*
Ok, off to trig where I fail. Whooo.
I'm out with Jessie. Yeah, you're jealous.

blah, blah, blah. ANYWAY. Too psych test today. Think I did alright. Dad's being an asshole, but what else is new. Hmm going to my cousin's birthday party tomorrow then out with my aunt and another aunt I haven't seen in awhile. and umm Saturday hopefully see Jessy and then go out with Suzana because I haven't seen her since Christmas! *cries* and Sunday I have Magic Mountain. Now to fix this fucking dsl...

I'm in preparations to make this lj friends only, so those of you who don't have ljs *pokes JT* better get one soon. :)

In other news, I just looked up UCSC's requirements for marine biology, and here's all the prereq's I gotta have before even sending an app:

Introductory requirements for the marine biology major are:

Biology 20A, Cell and Molecular Biology, 20B, Development and Physiology, and 20C, Ecology and Evolution

Chemistry 1B/M and 1C/N, General Chemistry with Laboratory (two quarters); and Chemistry 108A/L and 108B/M, Organic Chemistry with Laboratory (two quarters)

Engineering 5, Statistics or 7, Biostatistics (one quarter)

Mathematics 11A-B, Calculus with Applications (two quarters) or Mathematics 19A-B, Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics (two quarters)

Physics 7A/L and 7B/M, Elementary Physics (two quarters) or two courses from Physics 6A/L, 6B/M, 6C/N, Introduction to Physics with Laboratory (three-quarter series)


Eeh...what did I get myself into?

So my DSL is down...fuckers. I can't get on for a long time because I only get so much dial up, so blah. I guess I have to actually get a life now. I am going to Glendale this weekend but we have to have this lame barbeque thing Friday and then Sunday is Magic Mountain (for the 3rd time this year hehe). I'm really really bummed out my dsl doesn't work. Ugh. So yeah, call me or text me or im me on my phone because I'm going to be totally bored. I have nothing to look forward to when I get home now except hw. Grr. And I still have 14 weeks of school left. Joy. At least I have something to look forward to in March, but that seems SO SO far away...grr. And I can't stop thinking about SC...I'm such a bitch...:'(

I haven't been very happy lately. Just very blah. Yeah, blah. Meh. Anyway, yeah. Bad stuff happened to friends. I get to see my sister this weekend and I'm going to Magic Mountain on Superbowl Sunday because hopefully nobody will be there yayyyy. My head hurts and I htae school and work and GAH! *dies*

I feel dead. Gah. I freaking HURT! I can't walk because my ankle keeps having these shooting pains and I bent my fingernail back halfway and it keeps bleeding spontaneously. And drama at home and school is evil and work sucks and I keep having the same freaking dream and I hate it! :-(

The return of drunk Kait tonight. whooo. Can't call Jenn though...how am I supposed to entertain myself? ;-)


Hmm what else? Seeing Jenn and her sis and Jessie tomorrow. Yay.
